# Auto detect text files and perform LF normalization
* text=auto

# Two artifacts are hashed as RAW BYTES and must survive checkout unchanged.
#
# The encoder directory: every file in it is digested before the model will load.
# Without -text, the `* text=auto` rule above rewrites tokenizer.json and the JSON
# configs to CRLF on a Windows clone (core.autocrlf=true is the platform default),
# the directory digest changes, and the encoder refuses to start with an artifact
# hash error — on a machine where nothing is actually wrong. It is invisible in the
# authoring checkout and does not reproduce on macOS or Linux.
models/bge-m3-int8/** -text

# The vector artifact: ProfileIndex.load() hashes this file's bytes against
# manifest.json. Git's binary auto-detection already spares it, but the rule is
# stated rather than inferred, because the failure mode is a startup error that
# reads like tampering.
data/artifacts/*.npz -text

# Note: config/*.json and data/*.json are ALSO sealed into the manifest, but those
# hashes are taken over canonically re-serialised JSON (see maoz_search/artifacts.py),
# so line-ending conversion cannot affect them. They deliberately need no rule here.
